{"action": "edit", "code": "def divide_box(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Divides a box of squares into four equal parts.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the output grid with the box divided into four equal parts.\n    \"\"\"\n    out = np.zeros_like(input_grid)\n    h, w = input_grid.shape\n    out[:h // 2, :w // 2] = input_grid[:h // 2, :w // 2]\n    out[h // 2:, :w // 2] = input_grid[h // 2:, :w // 2]\n    out[:h // 2, w // 2:] = input_grid[:h // 2, w // 2:]\n    out[h // 2:, w // 2:] = input_grid[h // 2:, w // 2:]\n    return out\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    out = divide_box(input_grid)\n    return out", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    out = `Divide a box of squares into four.`(input_grid)\n    return out\n", "gpt_code": "def divide_box(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Divides a box of squares into four equal parts.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the output grid with the box divided into four equal parts.\n    \"\"\"\n    out = np.zeros_like(input_grid)\n    h, w = input_grid.shape\n    out[:h // 2, :w // 2] = input_grid[:h // 2, :w // 2]\n    out[h // 2:, :w // 2] = input_grid[h // 2:, :w // 2]\n    out[:h // 2, w // 2:] = input_grid[:h // 2, w // 2:]\n    out[h // 2:, w // 2:] = input_grid[h // 2:, w // 2:]\n    return out", "holes": {"divide_box": "Divide a box of squares into four."}}
